@node features "Features"

                               Features

-There's no complex installation: just run the game and play!

-MLink is a "Workbench" game, so it's meant to be played on the
 Workbench screen. The game window can be resized up to a maximum of
 480 x 300 pixels, and the game is redisplayed according to the new
 window size. If the window is too small, it will automatically be
 resized to an adequate displayable size.

-As the game uses as little of the computer's ressources as possible,
 you can run other applications, games, etc. at the same time.

-MLink works on all Amigas with Workbench 1.3 or higher.

@endnode

@node histo "History"

                               Versions History

  What follows are the various updates that were done since the first version
of this game.

1.0: -First release.

1.1: -No more blitting operations, just simple drawings, it's more friendly
      for blitter handicapped systems (Pegasos/Morphos, Amithlon, etc.)...
      and the display updates (when the game starts or if you resize the
      window) are faster.

1.11: -Some minor changes were made to the program code.
      -Some cosmetic changes were made (the pull-down menus were enhanced,
       the buttons were redrawn).

1.12: -Various changes have been made to the program code: the routine to
       generate the main game window has been revised, unneeded program
       code has been removed, etc.

1.13: -Some enhancement have been made to the program code.

2.0: -The arrows, used to move the tiles, have been removed. Now you can
      click directly on the tiles to move them where you want.
     -Some other code change have been made.

@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "MLink" where you want 
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. You must have a
Workbench with @{b}8 colours or more@{ub} to play the game, apart from that,
no other files or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  The game consists of 15 coloured chainlinks that were randomly shuffled.
You have to place these chainlinks in the right order, obviously with the
top ones (the upper 'semicircles') on the top, the lower ones (the lower
'semicircles') below and the intermediate links in between. Of course
their colour must match in each column...

  Note that you don't have to place the chains in a specific colour order
from left to right and the shorter chain can be placed either in the upper
or lower position in its column, as long as its links are joined together.

  Playing with MLink is very simple: A chainlink can move up or down if it
is located under or over the empty space, clicking on it will move the
chainlink towards the empty space.

  You can also move all chainlinks on the upper or bottom rows. To move
chainlinks to the left, click on one of the 2 leftmost tiles, and to move
chainlinks to the right, click on one of the 2 rightmost tiles of the
choosen row. If a chainlink or the empty space is located on one edge, it
will go to the other edge. Please note that if you click on a chainlink
located on the top or bottom row and the empty space is located under or
over that chainlink, then the chainlink will go towards the empty space
instead.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub} button (or
with the Right-Amiga + "N" key combination).

  Have fun!

@endnode

